Package: curvenumber
Title: An implementation of the USDA Soil Conservation Service Curve Number method
Version: 0.4.0
Authors@R: c(person("Claudia", "Vitolo", email = "cvitolodev@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
             person("Nataliya", "Le Vine", role = "ctb"), person("Irucka", "Embry", role = "ctb"))
Maintainer: Claudia Vitolo <cvitolodev@gmail.com>
URL: http://cvitolo.github.io/curvenumber/
BugReports: https://github.com/cvitolo/curvenumber/issues
Description: This package is an implementation of the Curve Number, a well
    established method for the estimation of direct runoff from storm rainfall.
    To install the Imported 'hydromad' package, use the following R code:
    'install.packages("hydromad", repos="http://hydromad.catchment.org")'.
    hydromad also makes use of the 'dream' package, in order to install 'dream',
    use the following R code:
    'install.packages("dream", repos="http://hydromad.catchment.org")'.
Depends: R (>= 3.0)
Imports: raster, pracma, xts, zoo, Hmisc, hydromad, minpack.lm, graphics, stats,
    utils, units, fpCompare, stringi, latticeExtra, polynom, car, reshape,
    DEoptim, data.table, assertthat, checkmate, round, rgdal, sp
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Repository: GitHub
Keywords: hydrology, hydrological modelling, hydrologic modeling, curve number
Suggests: devtools, knitr, rmarkdown, testthat, covr, ramify
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
